<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 4:49PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A cluster of thunderstorms will impact portions of central
Yellowstone County through 530 PM MDT...
At 447 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of thunderstorms
near Worden, or 16 miles northeast of Billings, moving northeast at
10 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects and vegetation is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Shepherd, Huntley, Worden, Ballantine and Pompeys Pillar. This also
includes motorists on I-94 east in the Huntley and Worden
vicinity.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
